Key Match Events: Paul George had nine points, four rebounds, eight assists and one steal while shooting 4/13 from the field and 0/6 from the three-point range in 25 minutes of playing time.
The 76ers lost by a score of 116-106 to fall to 1-7 in their first eight games.
Post-Match Reflections: Many NBA fans reacted to Paul George's performance, with some suggesting it might be time for him to retire.
Criticism included comments on his poor shooting performance and questioning his value as a primary scorer.
